usdPolicyMIB.name: usdPolicyMIB

revisions.description: Extended rate limit profile objects. Added traffic class rule objects. Obsoleted policy traffic shaped objects.
Added TCP flag and IP flag support objects. Replaced usdPolicyProfileTable with usdPolicyAttachProfileTable. Created new confomance groupings.

Added color rule objects. Added Local Input Policy ID and Local Input Stats Enable objects to the usdPolicyProfileTable. Replaced usdPolicyIfTable with usdPolicyIfAttachTable. Replaced usdPolicyIfStatsTable with usdPolicyIfAttachStatsTable.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdPolicyMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPolicyMIB.description: The Policy MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

UsdClaclPortOperator.name: UsdClaclPortOperator
UsdClaclPortOperator.description: Enumerates valid operators for use as source and destination port operators within a classifier control list.

UsdPolicyAttachmentType.name: UsdPolicyAttachmentType
UsdPolicyAttachmentType.description: Enumerates the types of policy attachments.

UsdPolicyForwardingType.name: UsdPolicyForwardingType
UsdPolicyForwardingType.description: Enumerates the type of forwarding to which the policy is applied.

UsdPolicyIpFragValue.name: UsdPolicyIpFragValue
UsdPolicyIpFragValue.description: Enumerates the values for IP frag offset classification.

UsdRateLimitProfileType.name: UsdRateLimitProfileType
UsdRateLimitProfileType.description: Enumerates the types of rate limit profiles.

usdPolicyNextIndex.name: usdPolicyNextIndex
usdPolicyNextIndex.description: This scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the usdPolicyTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

usdPolicyTable.name: usdPolicyTable
usdPolicyTable.description: This table contains entries which represent the non-repetive fields of a policy definition.

usdPolicyEntry.name: usdPolicyEntry
usdPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains the non-repetitive fields of a policy definition.

usdPolicyId.name: usdPolicyId
usdPolicyId.description: The number of the policy table entry which is defined by this row.

usdPolicyRowStatus.name: usdPolicyRowStatus
usdPolicyRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

usdPolicyAdminState.name: usdPolicyAdminState
usdPolicyAdminState.description: This object is used to control the administrative state of a policy. Enabling a policy will result in the rules which make up a policy being applied to interfaces to which the policy is assigned. Disabling a policy results in the the policy being taken out of service. This object may be modified while the row is active.

usdPolicyOperStatus.name: usdPolicyOperStatus
usdPolicyOperStatus.description: This object is used to retrieve the operational state of a policy. If a policy is disabled, it is not applied to any interfaces within the system. If a policy is invalid, there is a problem with the policy preventing it from being applied to an interface. An error code providing diagnostic information about the problem is found in usdPolicyErrorValue. If a policy is enabled, it has been applied to one or more interfaces within the system.

usdPolicyErrorValue.name: usdPolicyErrorValue
usdPolicyErrorValue.description: An error code providing diagnostic information for invalid policies. The enumeration of this field is TBD. A zero (0) value indicates that there is no error reported.

usdPolicyName.name: usdPolicyName
usdPolicyName.description: Specifies the name of the policy defined by this row.

usdPolicyReferenceCount.name: usdPolicyReferenceCount
usdPolicyReferenceCount.description: Reflects the number of times this policy has been applied within the chassis.

usdPolicyRuleNextIndex.name: usdPolicyRuleNextIndex
usdPolicyRuleNextIndex.description: Read only variable which provides the next available PolicyRuleIndex with respect to the policy defined by this row. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

usdPolicyRuleTable.name: usdPolicyRuleTable
usdPolicyRuleTable.description: Each entry within this table defines a rule component of a policy. The entries in this table are created automatically when entries are created in specific rule tables. This table is read only

usdPolicyRuleEntry.name: usdPolicyRuleEntry
usdPolicyRuleEntry.description: Each entry defines a single rule component.

usdPolicyRulePolicyId.name: usdPolicyRulePolicyId
usdPolicyRulePolicyId.description: The PolicyTable index of the policy which owns this rule.

usdPolicyRulePrec.name: usdPolicyRulePrec
usdPolicyRulePrec.description: The precedence of this rule within this group of policy rules.

usdPolicyRuleId.name: usdPolicyRuleId
usdPolicyRuleId.description: The index of this rule within the set of rules owned by the policy defined by usdPolicyRulePolicyId.

usdPolicyRuleType.name: usdPolicyRuleType
usdPolicyRuleType.description: This field specifies the type of rule being defined. The remaining information which makes up this rule is found in the specific rule table defined by usdPolicyRuleType. The specific rule tables are indexed by usdPolicyRulePolicyId.usdPolicyRuleId.

usdPolicySuspend.name: usdPolicySuspend
usdPolicySuspend.description: Setting this object to true results in the rule being suspended (taken out of service). Setting this value to false results in the rule being returned to service.

usdPolicyEclipsed.name: usdPolicyEclipsed
usdPolicyEclipsed.description: This value is true if the policy rule is eclipsed. A policy rule is eclipsed if a conflicting rule with the same classifier control list precedes the rule, and the preceding rule is not suspended. A false value indicates that the rule is not eclipsed.

usdNextHopRuleTable.name: usdNextHopRuleTable
usdNextHopRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide next-hop rule data. Rows created in this table result in an entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdNextHopRowStatus.name: usdNextHopRowStatus
usdNextHopRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The next-hop IP address is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdNextHopIpAddress.name: usdNextHopIpAddress
usdNextHopIpAddress.description: The IP address to forward all packets to.

usdNextHopClaclId.name: usdNextHopClaclId
usdNextHopClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which completes the NextHop policy rule.

usdFilterRuleTable.name: usdFilterRuleTable
usdFilterRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide filter rule data. Creation of an entry in this table results in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdFilterRowStatus.name: usdFilterRowStatus
usdFilterRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdFilterClaclId.name: usdFilterClaclId
usdFilterClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which completes the filter policy rule.

usdNextInterfaceRuleTable.name: usdNextInterfaceRuleTable
usdNextInterfaceRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide NextInterface rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdNextInterfaceRowStatus.name: usdNextInterfaceRowStatus
usdNextInterfaceRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The next-interface parameter is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdNextInterfaceId.name: usdNextInterfaceId
usdNextInterfaceId.description: The interface index to which traffic matching the CLACL ID will be routed.

usdNextInterfaceClaclId.name: usdNextInterfaceClaclId
usdNextInterfaceClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which completes the NextInterface policy rule.

usdNextInterfaceNextHop.name: usdNextInterfaceNextHop
usdNextInterfaceNextHop.description: The IP address to forward all packets to.

usdRateLimitRuleTable.name: usdRateLimitRuleTable
usdRateLimitRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide RateLimit rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdRateLimitRowStatus.name: usdRateLimitRowStatus
usdRateLimitRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The rate limit profile ID is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdRateLimitId.name: usdRateLimitId
usdRateLimitId.description: The RLP ID which provides the rate limit data which completes the RateLimit policy rule.

usdRateLimitClaclId.name: usdRateLimitClaclId
usdRateLimitClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which fills out the RateLimit policy rule.

usdMarkingRuleTable.name: usdMarkingRuleTable
usdMarkingRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide Marking rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdMarkingRowStatus.name: usdMarkingRowStatus
usdMarkingRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The IP precedence field is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdMarkingTOSByte.name: usdMarkingTOSByte
usdMarkingTOSByte.description: The IP precedence value associated with this policy rule.

usdMarkingMask.name: usdMarkingMask
usdMarkingMask.description: The mask to use for TOS byte checks.

usdMarkingClaclId.name: usdMarkingClaclId
usdMarkingClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which fills out the Marking policy rule.

usdForwardRuleTable.name: usdForwardRuleTable
usdForwardRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide forward rule data. Creation of an entry in this table results in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdForwardRowStatus.name: usdForwardRowStatus
usdForwardRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdForwardClaclId.name: usdForwardClaclId
usdForwardClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which completes the forward policy rule.

usdTrafficShapeRuleTable.name: usdTrafficShapeRuleTable
usdTrafficShapeRuleTable.description: Obsolete list of entries which provide Traffic Shape rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table. This list became obsolete when the policy shaper capability was moved into the quality of service component.

usdTrafficShapeRowStatus.name: usdTrafficShapeRowStatus
usdTrafficShapeRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The traffic shape profile ID is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdTrafficShapeId.name: usdTrafficShapeId
usdTrafficShapeId.description: The RLP ID which provides the rate limit data which completes the traffic shape policy rule.

usdColorRuleTable.name: usdColorRuleTable
usdColorRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide Color rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdColorRowStatus.name: usdColorRowStatus
usdColorRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The color field is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdColor.name: usdColor
usdColor.description: The color with which to explicitly color packets associated with this policy rule.

usdColorClaclId.name: usdColorClaclId
usdColorClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which fills out the Color policy rule.

usdLogRuleTable.name: usdLogRuleTable
usdLogRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide log rule data. Creation of an entry in this table results in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdLogRowStatus.name: usdLogRowStatus
usdLogRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdLogClaclId.name: usdLogClaclId
usdLogClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which completes the log policy rule.

usdTrafficClassRuleTable.name: usdTrafficClassRuleTable
usdTrafficClassRuleTable.description: A list of entries which provide traffic Class rule data. Creation of entries in the table result in a corresponding entry being created in the policy rule table.

usdTrafficClassRowStatus.name: usdTrafficClassRowStatus
usdTrafficClassRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. The usdTrafficClassId field is mandatory and must be specified. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy.

usdTrafficClassClaclId.name: usdTrafficClassClaclId
usdTrafficClassClaclId.description: The classifier control list ID which fills out the traffic class policy rule.

usdRateLimitProfileNextIndex.name: usdRateLimitProfileNextIndex
usdRateLimitProfileNextIndex.description: This scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the usdRateLimitProfileTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

usdRateLimitProfileTable.name: usdRateLimitProfileTable
usdRateLimitProfileTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of Rate Limit Profile (RLP) definitions.

usdRateLimitProfileEntry.name: usdRateLimitProfileEntry
usdRateLimitProfileEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a rate limit profile element.

usdRateLimitProfileId.name: usdRateLimitProfileId
usdRateLimitProfileId.description: The ID number of the rate limit profile (RLP) entry which is defined by this row.

usdRateLimitProfileRowStatus.name: usdRateLimitProfileRowStatus
usdRateLimitProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. All rowStatus modes are supported. To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdRateLimitProfileName

usdRateLimitProfileName.name: usdRateLimitProfileName
usdRateLimitProfileName.description: Specifies the name of the rate limit profile defined by this row.

usdRateLimitReferenceCount.name: usdRateLimitReferenceCount
usdRateLimitReferenceCount.description: This object reflects the number of times a rate limit profile object is referenced by policies.

usdRateLimitCommittedBps.name: usdRateLimitCommittedBps
usdRateLimitCommittedBps.description: The committed access rate in bits per second.

usdRateLimitCommittedBurst.name: usdRateLimitCommittedBurst
usdRateLimitCommittedBurst.description: The committed access rate burst value in bytes.

usdRateLimitExceedBps.name: usdRateLimitExceedBps
usdRateLimitExceedBps.description: The peak access rate in bits per second. To be configured only if rate limit profile type is two-rate.

usdRateLimitExceedBurst.name: usdRateLimitExceedBurst
usdRateLimitExceedBurst.description: The peak access rate burst value in bytes. To be configured only if rate limit profile type is two-rate.

usdRateLimitCommittedAction.name: usdRateLimitCommittedAction
usdRateLimitCommittedAction.description: Action to be taken when the access rate is within the bounds of the committed access rate.

usdRateLimitConformedAction.name: usdRateLimitConformedAction
usdRateLimitConformedAction.description: Action to be taken when the access rate exceeds the bounds of the committed access rate.

usdRateLimitExceededAction.name: usdRateLimitExceededAction
usdRateLimitExceededAction.description: Action to be taken when the access rate exceeds the bounds of the peak access rate.

usdRateLimitCommittedMarkVal.name: usdRateLimitCommittedMarkVal
usdRateLimitCommittedMarkVal.description: New IP precedence to be used when the usdRateLimitCommittedAction mark action is applied.

usdRateLimitConformedMarkVal.name: usdRateLimitConformedMarkVal
usdRateLimitConformedMarkVal.description: New IP prececence to be used when the usdRateLimitExceedCommittedAction mark action is applied.

usdRateLimitExceededMarkVal.name: usdRateLimitExceededMarkVal
usdRateLimitExceededMarkVal.description: New IP precedence to be used when the usdRateLimitExceedPeakAction mark action is applied.

usdRateLimitMask.name: usdRateLimitMask
usdRateLimitMask.description: Mask to be applied when executing a mark action.

usdRateLimitProfileType.name: usdRateLimitProfileType
usdRateLimitProfileType.description: The rate limit profile type (i.e. one-rate or two-rate). Defaults to two-rate, if not specified.

usdRateLimitExcessBurst.name: usdRateLimitExcessBurst
usdRateLimitExcessBurst.description: The excess committed access rate burst value in bytes. To be configured only if rate limit profile type is one-rate.

usdTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex
usdTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex.description: Obsolete scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the usdTrafficShapeProfileTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended. This object became obsolete when the policy shaper capability was moved into the quality of service component.

usdTrafficShapeProfileTable.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileTable
usdTrafficShapeProfileTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of Traffic Shape Profile definitions. This table became obsolete when the policy shaper capability was moved into the quality of service component.

usdTrafficShapeProfileEntry.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileEntry
usdTrafficShapeProfileEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a traffic shape profile element.

usdTrafficShapeProfileId.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileId
usdTrafficShapeProfileId.description: The number of the traffic shape profile entry which is defined by this row.

usdTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus
usdTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. All rowStatus modes are supported. To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus

usdTrafficShapeProfileName.name: usdTrafficShapeProfileName
usdTrafficShapeProfileName.description: Specifies the name of the traffic shape profile defined by this row.

usdTrafficShapeReferenceCount.name: usdTrafficShapeReferenceCount
usdTrafficShapeReferenceCount.description: This object reflects the number of times a traffic shape profile object is referenced by policies.

usdTrafficShapeRate.name: usdTrafficShapeRate
usdTrafficShapeRate.description: The traffic shape rate in bits per second.

usdTrafficShapeBurst.name: usdTrafficShapeBurst
usdTrafficShapeBurst.description: The traffic shape burst in bytes.

usdClassifierControlListNextIndex.name: usdClassifierControlListNextIndex
usdClassifierControlListNextIndex.description: This scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the usdClassifierControlListTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

usdClassifierControlListTable.name: usdClassifierControlListTable
usdClassifierControlListTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of classifier control lists. The details pertinent to each CLACL are found in the usdClassifierControlDefTable.

usdClassifierControlListEntry.name: usdClassifierControlListEntry
usdClassifierControlListEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an IP access list element.

usdClassifierControlListId.name: usdClassifierControlListId
usdClassifierControlListId.description: The number of the classifier control list to which this entry belongs.

usdClassifierControlListRowStatus.name: usdClassifierControlListRowStatus
usdClassifierControlListRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy. To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdClassifierControlListRowStatus usdClassifierControlListElemId

usdClassifierControlListName.name: usdClassifierControlListName
usdClassifierControlListName.description: The name of the CLACL being defined.

usdClassifierControlListReferenceCount.name: usdClassifierControlListReferenceCount
usdClassifierControlListReferenceCount.description: Number of times this CLACL is referenced by policies.

usdClassifierControlListNextElementIndex.name: usdClassifierControlListNextElementIndex
usdClassifierControlListNextElementIndex.description: Each get of this object will return a unique index which may be used to create classifier control list elements. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

usdClassifierControlListElementTable.name: usdClassifierControlListElementTable
usdClassifierControlListElementTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of classifier control lists. Entries belonging to the same control list are ordered, and comparisons to those entries are performed in that order until a match is detected. If no match is found, the default action is to 'deny'.

usdClassifierControlListElementEntry.name: usdClassifierControlListElementEntry
usdClassifierControlListElementEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an IP access list element.

usdClassifierControlListElemId.name: usdClassifierControlListElemId
usdClassifierControlListElemId.description: The relative position of this entry within its classifier control list. Classifier control list entries are searched in this sequence (low to high values) until a match is found.

usdClassifierControlListElemRowStatus.name: usdClassifierControlListElemRowStatus
usdClassifierControlListElemRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. This table provides a partial implementation for rowStatus. Rows may be created using createAndGo and createAndWait. Once a row has been made active the row status may not be changed.

usdClassifierControlListNotSrc.name: usdClassifierControlListNotSrc
usdClassifierControlListNotSrc.description: Invert the meaning of the source IP address and mask objects. For example 'not 10.10.0.90/255.255.255.255 (host address)' would result in all source addresses except for host 10.19.9.90 being matched.

usdClassifierControlListSrc.name: usdClassifierControlListSrc
usdClassifierControlListSrc.description: A source IP address. A subject IP address is first masked with the value of usdClassifierControlListSrcMask, then the result is compared to this value. Setting both this object and its corresponding mask to 0.0.0.0 acts as a wildcard, matching any source IP address.

usdClassifierControlListSrcMask.name: usdClassifierControlListSrcMask
usdClassifierControlListSrcMask.description: The IP address mask to be applied to a subject source IP address before comparing it to usdClassifierControlListSrc. Ones in the mask identify which bits in the subject IP address are significant for the comparison. To be considered valid, a nonzero value for this object must contain a single contiguous string of ones, beginning with the most significant bit of the mask.

usdClassifierControlListNotDst.name: usdClassifierControlListNotDst
usdClassifierControlListNotDst.description: Invert the meaning of the destination IP address and mask objects. For example, 'not 10.10.0.90/255.255.255.255 (host address)' would result in all source addresses except for host 10.19.9.90 being matched.

usdClassifierControlListDst.name: usdClassifierControlListDst
usdClassifierControlListDst.description: A destination IP address. A subject IP address is first masked with the value of usdClassifierControlListDstMask, then the result is compared to this value. Setting both this object and its corresponding mask to 0.0.0.0 acts as a wildcard, matching any destination IP address.

usdClassifierControlListDstMask.name: usdClassifierControlListDstMask
usdClassifierControlListDstMask.description: The IP address mask to be applied to a subject destination IP address before comparing it to usdClassifierControlListDst. Ones in the mask identify which bits in the IP address are significant for the comparison. To be considered valid, a nonzero value for this object must contain a single contiguous string of ones, beginning with the most significant bit of the mask.

usdClassifierControlListNotProtocol.name: usdClassifierControlListNotProtocol
usdClassifierControlListNotProtocol.description: Invert the meaning of the protocol object. For example, 'not TCP' matches any protocol except for TCP.

usdClassifierControlListProtocol.name: usdClassifierControlListProtocol
usdClassifierControlListProtocol.description: An IP Protocol value. Nonzero values match a specific IP Protocol value (e.g. 6 for TCP) carried in an IP packet; a value of zero acts as a wildcard, matching any IP Protocol.

usdClassifierControlListTosByte.name: usdClassifierControlListTosByte
usdClassifierControlListTosByte.description: The IP TOS byte value to match.

usdClassifierControlListMask.name: usdClassifierControlListMask
usdClassifierControlListMask.description: The mask to use for TOS byte checks. Allowed values are 0, 224, 252, 255.

usdClassifierControlListSrcOperator.name: usdClassifierControlListSrcOperator
usdClassifierControlListSrcOperator.description: Operator for use in comparing source ports.

usdClassifierControlListSrcFromPort.name: usdClassifierControlListSrcFromPort
usdClassifierControlListSrcFromPort.description: Source UDP or TCP 'from' port number.

usdClassifierControlListSrcToPort.name: usdClassifierControlListSrcToPort
usdClassifierControlListSrcToPort.description: Source UDP or TCP 'to' port number.

usdClassifierControlListDestOperator.name: usdClassifierControlListDestOperator
usdClassifierControlListDestOperator.description: Operator for use in comparing Destination ports.

usdClassifierControlListDestFromPort.name: usdClassifierControlListDestFromPort
usdClassifierControlListDestFromPort.description: Destination UDP or TCP 'from' port number.

usdClassifierControlListDestToPort.name: usdClassifierControlListDestToPort
usdClassifierControlListDestToPort.description: Destination UDP or TCP 'to' port number.

usdClassifierControlListICMPType.name: usdClassifierControlListICMPType
usdClassifierControlListICMPType.description: Optional ICMP message type for classification.

usdClassifierControlListICMPCode.name: usdClassifierControlListICMPCode
usdClassifierControlListICMPCode.description: Optional ICMP message code for classification.

usdClassifierControlListIGMPType.name: usdClassifierControlListIGMPType
usdClassifierControlListIGMPType.description: Optional IGMP message type for classification.

usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue.name: usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue
usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue.description: Optional TCP flags value for classification.

usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask.name: usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask
usdClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask.description: Optional TCP flags mask for classification. TCP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits.

usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue.name: usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue
usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue.description: Optional IP flags value for classification.

usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask.name: usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask
usdClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask.description: Optional IP flags mask for classification. IP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits

usdClassifierControlListIpFragValue.name: usdClassifierControlListIpFragValue
usdClassifierControlListIpFragValue.description: Optional IP flags mask for classification. IP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits

usdPolicyIfTable.name: usdPolicyIfTable
usdPolicyIfTable.description: This obsolete table contains entries which represent attachment of policies to interfaces. This table became obsolete when the usdPolicyIfAttTable was added.

usdPolicyIfEntry.name: usdPolicyIfEntry
usdPolicyIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the attachment of policy(s) to an interface.

usdPolicyIfInterfaceId.name: usdPolicyIfInterfaceId
usdPolicyIfInterfaceId.description: The interface number representing the interface to which policy(s) have been attached.

usdPolicyIfRowStatus.name: usdPolicyIfRowStatus
usdPolicyIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

usdPolicyIfInputPolicyId.name: usdPolicyIfInputPolicyId
usdPolicyIfInputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of input policies to the interface specified by usdPolicyIfInterfaceId, usdPolicyIfForwardingType and usdPolicyIfPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

usdPolicyIfOutputPolicyId.name: usdPolicyIfOutputPolicyId
usdPolicyIfOutputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of output policies to the interface specified by usdPolicyIfInterfaceId, usdPolicyIfForwardingType and usdPolicyIfPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

usdPolicyIfInputStatsEnable.name: usdPolicyIfInputStatsEnable
usdPolicyIfInputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an input policy attachment. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of usdPolicyInputStatsEnable.

usdPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable.name: usdPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable
usdPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an output policy attachment. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of usdPolicyOutputStatsEnable.

usdPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId.name: usdPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId

usdPolicyIfAttachForwardingType.name: usdPolicyIfAttachForwardingType

usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyType.name: usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyType

usdPolicyIfAttachRowStatus.name: usdPolicyIfAttachRowStatus
usdPolicyIfAttachRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyId.name: usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyId
usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of policies to the interface specified by usdPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId, usdPolicyIfAttachForwardingType and usdPolicyIfAttachPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

usdPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable.name: usdPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable
